1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents an algorithm for generating the binary expansion of an absolutely normal number with a nearly linear time complexity. This falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory): The concept of absolutely normal numbers is related to information theory, as it deals with the frequency of occurrence of strings of digits in the base-b expansion of a real number. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithm for generating absolutely normal numbers, which is an important aspect of computational complexity theory.
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The algorithm presented in the paper involves numerical computations and diagonalization of a martingale, which falls under the scope of numerical analysis.
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The concept of absolutely normal numbers is related to discrete mathematics, as it deals with the frequency of occurrence of strings of digits in the base-b expansion of a real number, which can be analyzed using combinatorial methods.
